Class BuiltinKeyEvent

  • All Implemented Interfaces:
    Sequenceable

    public abstract class BuiltinKeyEvent
extends KeyEvent
    Defines the key events of internal input devices.

    Key events of all internal input devices, such as buttons on the TV, and vehicle, and knobs, are all defined by this class. The OS manages key events of internal input devices in a unified manner. Permissions have been granted for keycodes defined in this class and its child classes. This means that access to key events requires the respective permissions.
